<title>UK: UK's Hague completes Conservative front bench team.</title>
<headline>UK's Hague completes Conservative front bench team.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Opposition Conservative leader William Hague on Tuesday completed his &quot;front bench&quot; team to shadow the Labour government and speak on key issues.</p>
<p>In addition to Peter Lilley as Shadow Chancellor and David Heathcoat-Amory as Shadow Chief Secretary, Hague appointed former junior agriculture minister Tim Boswell as a treasury front bench spokesman, his office said in a statement.</p>
<p>Hague also appointed the chairman of supermarket group ASDA, Archie Norman, now Conservative member of parliament for Tunbridge Wells, to the party's central office as a vice chairman to deal with party organisation.  </p>
<p>Norman will work alongside Alan Duncan, also appointed vice-chairman, who will deal with the media, as well as deputy chairman Michael Trend and chairman Lord Parkinson.</p>
